        "contentHtml": "<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">1. Remove a Watch Face Directly on Your Watch</h2><p style=\"text-align: left;\">This is the quickest way and works on most Garmin devices, such as the <strong>Venu</strong>, <strong>Forerunner</strong>, and <strong>Fenix</strong> series.</p><h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">Steps:</h3><ol><li style=\"text-align: left;\">Wake up your watch and go to the main watch face.</li><li style=\"text-align: left;\">Press and hold the screen (usually 1–2 seconds).</li><li style=\"text-align: left;\">Select “Watch Face” from the menu.</li><li style=\"text-align: left;\">Scroll through your list of installed watch faces.</li><li style=\"text-align: left;\">Highlight the one you want to remove.</li><li style=\"text-align: left;\">Select “Delete” or “Remove.”</li></ol><p><br></p><h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">2. Remove a Watch Face via the Garmin Connect IQ App</h2><p style=\"text-align: left;\">If you prefer managing your watch from your phone, you can delete a watch face through the <strong>Garmin Connect IQ</strong> mobile app.</p><h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">Steps:</h3><ol><li style=\"text-align: left;\">Open the Garmin Connect IQ app on your smartphone.</li><li style=\"text-align: left;\">Tap the “My Device” tab at the bottom.</li><li style=\"text-align: left;\">Select your Garmin watch model.</li><li style=\"text-align: left;\">Tap “Installed Apps.”</li><li style=\"text-align: left;\">Find the watch face you want to remove (e.g., Wristo – Daily Garland).</li><li style=\"text-align: left;\">Tap it, then choose “Remove” or “Uninstall.”</li><li style=\"text-align: left;\">Confirm and allow the app to sync with your watch.</li><li style=\"text-align: left;\">After syncing, the watch face will be deleted automatically.</li></ol><p><br></p><h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">3. Remove a Watch Face Using Garmin Express (Desktop)</h2><p style=\"text-align: left;\">You can also manage and remove apps or watch faces via <strong>Garmin Express</strong> on your computer.</p><h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">Steps:</h3><ol><li style=\"text-align: left;\">Open Garmin Express on your PC or Mac.</li><li style=\"text-align: left;\">Connect your watch to your computer using a USB cable.</li><li style=\"text-align: left;\">Select your device → click the “Apps” tab.</li><li style=\"text-align: left;\">Find the watch face you want to remove.</li><li style=\"text-align: left;\">Click “Remove” and save changes.</li><li style=\"text-align: left;\">Once syncing is complete, the watch face will be uninstalled from your device.</li></ol><p><br></p><h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">4. Common Questions</h2><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Q: Can I reinstall a deleted watch face later?</strong><br><br>A: Yes! You can always reinstall it from the Garmin Connect IQ app at any time.</p><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Q: Will removing a watch face affect my other settings or apps?</strong><br><br>A: No. Watch faces are separate from your system settings, so deleting one won’t impact other apps.</p><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Q: The watch face still appears after I deleted it — what should I do?</strong><br><br>A: Try syncing your watch manually or restarting the device to clear cached data.</p>"
